Juan Carlos Cardona Rivas (born July 7, 1974 in Jardin, Antioquia) is a male marathon runner from Colombia, who twice represented his native country in the men's marathon at the Summer Olympics (2004 and 2008). He won the 2007 edition of the Buenos Aires Marathon in Argentina.  
